  (863, 'What size backup generator does my Pacific Palisades business need?', 'The right generator size depends on your facility''s power requirements, which vary based on your industry, equipment, and operational priorities. Our engineers conduct a detailed load analysis of your Pacific Palisades property, identifying critical systems that must remain powered and calculating total demand. We then recommend a appropriately sized unit—whether that''s a 20 kW system for a small office or a 150+ kW unit for a larger facility or restaurant. We handle the entire assessment at no charge.', 1),

  (863, 'Can Shaffer Construction handle all permitting and inspections for my Pacific Palisades generator installation?', 'Yes, we manage the complete permitting and inspection process for commercial backup generator installations in Pacific Palisades. Our team (licensed A, B, and C-10) ensures your system complies with all local electrical codes and city requirements, including utility interconnection standards. We coordinate with inspectors and handle all paperwork, so you can focus on your business while we ensure everything meets code.', 2),

  (863, 'How often should my commercial backup generator in Pacific Palisades be serviced?', 'Commercial backup generators typically require quarterly maintenance and annual load testing to ensure reliable operation when you need it most. We recommend monthly self-tests and seasonal inspections before peak usage periods. Shaffer Construction provides comprehensive maintenance packages that keep your system running smoothly, extend equipment life, and give you the confidence that your generator will perform during an emergency. Contact us to set up a service schedule tailored to your business.', 3),

  (863, 'What are the benefits of remote monitoring for my Pacific Palisades commercial generator?', 'Remote monitoring systems allow you and our team to track your generator''s status 24/7, receiving automatic alerts if maintenance is needed or if the system activates during an outage. This technology is especially valuable for Pacific Palisades business owners who travel or manage multiple properties. You''ll have real-time visibility into fuel levels, system health, and operational status—all from your phone or computer. Shaffer Construction can integrate monitoring into your installation for added peace of mind and operational efficiency.', 4);

